&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;RPA is seeking a Manager of Analytics to lead reporting and insights for a major account. This role owns end-to-end performance reporting, delivers strategic insights, and drives proactive communication across cross-functional teams. As a highly client-facing role, strong presentation and communication skills are essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is analytically strong, collaborative, and solutions-oriented, with a positive, professional approach and strong interpersonal skills. They build trust across teams, communicate proactively, and thrive in fast-paced environments. While the required technical and analytical skills outlined in the job description are critical, true success in this role will come from a genuine motivation to support a highly engaged client in achieving their business and marketing goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who is excited to support our clients and work closely alongside the media team, and contribute to the continued growth of the account. The ideal candidate is curious and forward-thinking, with a passion for improving workflows, building smarter solutions, and leveraging AI and automation to drive efficiency and innovation across the analytics process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Manage weekly client dashboards, ensuring data is ingested properly, QA’d, reconciled, and delivered accurately&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Own monthly reporting from start to finish, including analysis, insights, and any internal and client presentations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Develop optimization recommendations and actionable insights&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Maintain project status tracking and communicate updates proactively&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Support executive and client presentations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Partner collaboratively with media, strategy, creative, and client teams&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Support additional analytics and reporting requests as needed&lt;/p&gt;
